{
  "stem": "10353.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] We were very, very knowledgeable about the rising of the Hitler era.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my father went for medical reasons, went to Berlin in 1931.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he came back in 1932.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember, as a-- as a kid, that he told us the story that there is some movement in Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there's this fellow by the name of Hitler that, if he comes to power, then it will be the demise-- it will be the demise of the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember, it was like a story, you know, that-- that you hear.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we, of course, we were very knowledgeable about finally what happened with Hitler getting into power and his marching into to-- to Vienna, to Austria, to conquer Austria.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "First of all, he took the Saarbrucken-- that was his first move that he took away from France, the Saar territory, and which followed by the invasion of Vienna, which later followed the demands of the Sudetenland, you know.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish people felt very, very much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And now, having said that the greatest majority of the population there were Hungarians, they rooted for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were-- but we were in trepidation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew what-- what was following.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so when they marched into Czechoslovakia, and they occupied the Sudetenland, we saw that the noose is gettin' tighter and tighter.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [BACKGROUND NOISE] We, of course, we were very well-aware of what happened-- the Sudetenland was decided at Munich.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we knew the episode with Chamberlain, and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we also, which was followed up by Germany demanding the Port of Danzig in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And prior to that, they had occupied-- there is a small port in Lithuania or Latvia-- I don't remember exactly-- which was called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they occupied [NON-ENGLISH], which followed by the demand of Danzig.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Poland would not relent.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And France and Britain was supporting Poland by not acceding to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Daily.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On a daily basis.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Daily, and practically, that occupied our-- out entire life, the conversation of-- of the political, and the situation that was going on and how it's culminating.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Finally, in 19-- [SIGHS] 39, I remember, I had-- I had finished my Judaic studies.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In 1939, we saw how the wind is blowing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And on September the 1st, we got to know that Hitler invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in relative-- in relative security at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we heard what was going on, and we felt very upset-- knowing what was happened to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we did not realize-- realize the extent of the danger that was really facing the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The first sense that we got about the great danger was already later on in-- in 19-- January, I believe, January, 1940.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Prior to that, in September, the 5th of 1940, we were occupied by the Hungarians, part of Transylvania was occupied by the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, overnight, we became Hungarian citizens, so to say.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were already allied with the Germans by that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And some anti-Jewish laws were coming out slowly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Like Jews, for instance, couldn't go to the market, shopping, till 10 o'clock to give-- to give more time for the non-Jewish population to go to the market first.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They wouldn't issue any new-- any licenses for Jewish businesses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the so-called undercurrent was coming through the surface.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there were anti-Semitic manifestations by more repeated beatings of Jews, and sort of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] physically abusing 'em.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] They probably did, but they didn't go too far.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For the Hungarians, you didn't go too far.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were-- was the Romanians-- you could buy your way out many times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You couldn't do that with the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were also dominated very strongly by the German anti-Jewish policies.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nonetheless, we could still breathe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We could still live, even though they have instituted, by that time, numerus nullus-- in other words, Jews couldn't-- Jews couldn't go to colleges.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A Jew couldn't open up a business, unless-- unless he couldn't employ-- a Jewish corporation couldn't employ Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He had to have 96% non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Only 6% could-- could be in managerial position-- only 6%.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You were relegated to manual work only.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But you lived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, the-- the war scene took a stranglehold.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Everything was rationed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Jews did not enjoy the same rationing as non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But you went around.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You worked around it, and you lived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In May of 19-- 1941, I decided to leave my hometown because Halmeu is a smaller town-- not small, it was about 80,000-- 80,000 to 100,000 inhabitants.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I moved up to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In Budapest--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By myself.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
